<pdd-reason>Interactive prompt checkup orchestration for explicit `pdd checkup --interactive` repair sessions.</pdd-reason>
<pdd-interface>
{
  "type": "module",
  "module": {
    "classes": [
      {
        "name": "ClickInteractiveSession",
        "kind": "class"
      }
    ],
    "functions": [
      {
        "name": "filter_interactive_findings",
        "signature": "(report: PromptSourceSetReport, *, explicit_interactive: bool) -> list[SourceSetFinding]",
        "returns": "list[SourceSetFinding]"
      },
      {
        "name": "build_repair_options_for_finding",
        "signature": "(finding: SourceSetFinding, *, project_root: Optional[Path] = None, fallback_target: Optional[Path] = None) -> list[RepairOption]",
        "returns": "list[RepairOption]"
      },
      {
        "name": "run_interactive_checkup",
        "signature": "(target: str, *, apply: bool = False, dry_run: bool = False, project_root: Optional[Path] = None, strict: bool = False, quiet: bool = False, explicit_interactive: bool = True, session_factory: Optional[Callable[[], InteractiveRepairSession]] = None) -> Optional[tuple[str, float, str]]",
        "returns": "Optional[tuple[str, float, str]]"
      }
    ]
  }
}
</pdd-interface>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_interactive_session_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_prompt_apply_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>
<pdd-dependency>checkup_prompt_main_python.prompt</pdd-dependency>

% Goal
Write `pdd/checkup_interactive_main.py`.

% Requirements
- Run only for explicit interactive prompt-checkup intent.
- Build a deterministic source-set report, seed an interactive repair session, present each in-scope finding, and optionally apply approved patches.
- Present repair choices as Option A, Option B, keep current / skip, custom fix, and rationale/details affordances.
- Non-explicit repair routing may include only findings where `requires_clarification=True`; explicit interactive mode may include all findings.
- Do not call an LLM in tests; use deterministic session factories and patch objects.
- Surface rejected patch application results truthfully in CLI output and return the applicator exit code.

<contract_rules>
R1 - Explicit interactive gate
This module is an interactive repair path and MUST NOT be the default for bare `pdd checkup <prompt>`.

R2 - Option affordances
The user-visible flow MUST offer Option A, Option B, keep current / skip, custom fix, and rationale/details.

R3 - Honest apply result
Rejected approved patches MUST be reported to the terminal and MUST propagate a non-zero result.
</contract_rules>

% Deliverables
- Code: `pdd/checkup_interactive_main.py`
